1.area of cylinder

radius=int(input("enter the radius:"))
height=float(input("enter the height:"))
pi=3.14
area =int(pi*radius*radius*height)
print("area of the cylinder with radius {} and height {} is area {}".format(radius,height,area))

O/P
enter the radius:2
enter the height:5
area of the cylinder with radius 2 and height 5.0 is area 62



2.Area and circumference of the circle

pi=3.14
radius=int(input("enter the radius:"))
area=int(pi*radius*radius)
circumference=2*pi*radius
print("area of the circle with radius {} is area {}".format(radius,area))
print("circumference of the circle with radius {} is circumference {}".format(radius,circumference))

O/P
enter the radius:12
area of the circle with radius 12 is area 452
circumference of the circle with radius 12 is circumference 75.36
